Posts: 1339

by Hatsunia » Fri Nov 15, 2019 10:55 pm

The space-based nation is divided into three layers. The first layer is 100 km to 500 km above Earth, with 20,000 space stations (most federal, residential, and agricultural stations). Orbits must be planned to avoid collisions, and there has only been one collision incident in 50 years. The second layer ranges from 500 km to 1000 km, and has stations manufacturing things from ships down to smaller goods. The third layer ranges from 1000 km to 1.5 million km, and holds a small number of automated stations and refueling depots for automated interplanetary vehicles. Luna is independent.
The first sound of the future, the society of the future
Japan missed the software revolution. Hatsunia embraced it.
